extends help-layout

block help-headcontent
  meta(name="description", content="Learn how to use tools with Help Linear Algebra")
  meta(property="og:title" content="Graph Linear Algebra | Help tools")
  meta(property="og:description" content="Learn how to use tools with Help Linear Algebra")

block help-content 
  section.nav-panel.wrapper
    h1.help-title= "Tools"
    p.description.
      The tools bar deals with miscellaneous topics such as dot product and determinant. 

  section.property.wrapper#dot-product
    h2.title="#dot-product"
    p.description.
      The dot product panel calculates the dot product between two vectors.

    div.subsection
      h4.subtitle=".vector-a, .vector-b"
      p.description.
        An expression that outputs a real vector.
      p.description.
        Valid expressions includes [1,2], [2+1, sin(pi)], etc. See the syntax <a href="https://mathjs.org/docs/expressions/syntax.html" target="_blank">here</a>.
      p.description.
        Vector a and vector b must have the same dimensions.
      p.description.
        This expression can contain vector variables in <a href="/help/vectors#list">vectors#list</a>
      

  section.property.wrapper#determinant 
    h2.title="#determinant"
    p.description.
      The determinant panel can display and calculate the determinant of the current transformation.
    p.description.
      The current transformation is the output of <a href="/help/matrices#transform">matrices#transform</a>.
      
    div.subsection
        h4.subtitle=".determinant"
        p.description.
          The current determinant of the transformation.

     div.subsection
        h4.subtitle=".display-determinant"
        p.description.
          When it is on, it would display a parallelogram from the column vectors of both the identity matrix and the current transformation. 

  section.property.wrapper#eigen 
    h2.title="#eigen"
    p.description.
      The eigen panel can display and calculate the eigenvalues and eigenvectors of the current transformation.
    p.description.
      The eigen panel is in BETA; its calculations may be bugged.
    p.description.
      Please email me at <a href="mailto:graphlinearalgebra@gmail.com">graphlinearalgebra@gmail.com</a> if you know a bug resistant way of calculating eigens.
    p.description.
      <strong><code>NaN</strong></code> does not necessary mean the eigenvector is nonexistent.
      
    div.subsection
        h4.subtitle=".display-eigenvectors"
        p.description.
          Displays purple lines that represent sets of eigenvectors of the transformation.
        p.description.
          The purple lines displayed does not all sets of valid eigenvectors. For example, matrix I does not display any lines.

     div.subsection
        h4.subtitle=".eig-1"
        p.description.
            The first pair of eigen values and vectors.

     div.subsection
        h4.subtitle=".eig-2"
        p.description.
            The second pair of eigen values and vectors.